<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by D23 on 04-25-2001 07:43 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Viperdice, I have known for a long time that it was bad mojo to attack something when it can't reach you. I don't see it listed anywhere, so if someone was new, I could see where they would get a warning their first time. But after getting notified once, that attacking from safe areas was a no no, then they have now been informed. That's why people are not banned on the first offense like this I guess.

Guardian, please tell me that you don't see your defining class ability as being able to summon a lvl 4 fire pet, or bandages? If it is, you just plain suck and are a whiny baby. Get a grip and learn how to play yoyr class. Hell, ANY class. Not many mages I know use the ability to summon bandages as a group bonus. At least no one over lvl 20 or so. As to me playing a lot, I have a 54 cleric, 50 warrior, 30 monk, and the rest under 20, Yeah, I play a bit. You think that the warrior is going to be able to fight off all the things he is going to aggro to the zone? Not really sure where the "rock" was you were fighting at, but if it is any distance at all, you are not going to be killing everything to get out. But all that is beside the point.
1) You were exploiting a bug.
2) You got caught.
3) You were told that you were going to eget a warning and to leave the area.
4) You tried to turn the talk around into a "Why my mage sucks" topic.

Does that about cover it?
Hell, I know that I helped a lvl 12 necro kill a hill giant sitting in the entrance to befallen way back in the day. I KNEW I was exploiting. There was no doubt in my mind. I helped to see how long it would take and to see if it would be worth it. If I had got into trouble for it, I would not have done it again and moved on. I would not have bitched at the GM for telling me.

Belinar, I think many people care about our opinions, otherwise, why would people bother to respond? This has nothing to do with whether I have ever exploited or not, it has to do with whining like a baby when you get caught. If I get pulled over for speeding, I don't get mad or bitch at the cop because I was going too fast.

Cheat, exploit, hack, dupe, I really don't care. Just grow a pair and take the punishment instead of crying and whining like a baby if you get caught.

</TEXTAREA>
